^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, the auction bears discussion. first of all, I was so excited that I could discuss why I play 1N forcing in 4th seat, that I missed my 1S bid, lol. 1S is a better bid by me. But let's take my 1N bid, and why it needs to be forcing if you don't play Drury. It is for hands like this (assuming I don't have a spade suit), where I have a limit raise with 3 card support. I have no way of showing that hand if I don't play that either 1N is forcing by a passed hand, or else I have to play Drury, so I can show the limit raise. |
PG| ***** 44 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, that is why if you play 1N is not forcing by a passed hand, you have to play Drury. I also play 1S is forcing, BTW even by a passed hand otherwise, the bidding is very difficult. Now, as to Patti's 4H bid. It was a very good bid. She was just done in by the terrible diamond break, and the Q of hearts being offside. Even though she only has 10 HCP, she has a great hand. Let's count her Bergen Points.  |
PG| ***** 45 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|10 HCP + two length points + one quality suit = 13 Starting Points. Once I raise hearts, she adds two for the singleton and one for the 4+ diamond side suit, which brings her to 16. So, she has a clear 4H bid. and she is a favorite to make 4H. So, nice bid Patti, even though you went down. More often than not you will score lots of IMPs on this board. |
PG| ***** 46 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One other point. Roberta should be very reluctant to lead a diamond. If diamonds were not bid, the diamond is a very good lead. However, in general, I try to avoid leading suits the opponents have bid. On this hand I would have chose a spade. Leading J from Jx is not that great either, but I think it rates to work out better on this auction.|
