^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, this hand merits discussion of the play. First let's discuss the opening lead. In general, as you know, leading unprotected Aces is a bad idea. However, leading from Qxx also often gives away a trick, particularly, because of my double, it is known to be in the opponents suit. And a singleton trump is also generally not a good idea, as it often picks up the suit for declarer. So East has a tough lead. My choice would have probably been the Ace of diamonds, since it is likely that pard has the K. My 2nd choice would have been a spade. It did turn out the heart was very favorable for declarer.|
